# Rux UI: CSS Architecture & Token System

## Core Philosophy

Rux UI uses a **Three-Tier Design Token System**. The tiers create a strict dependency chain:

```
Tier 1 Primitives  →  Tier 2 Semantics  →  Tier 3 Component
(variables.css)        (variables.css)        (component file)
```

`variables.css` contains only Tiers 1 and 2. Component-specific tokens always live
in their own CSS file. This keeps `variables.css` short, scannable, and stable.

---

## Tier 1 — Primitives

**Purpose:** Raw values. No semantic meaning. The source of truth for every scale.

**Location:** `:root` in `variables.css`

**Naming:** `--rux-{category}-{key}`

| Category | Prefix | Example |
|----------|--------|---------|
| Color seeds | `--rux-color-` | `--rux-color-blue` |
| Font families | `--rux-font-` | `--rux-font-sans` |
| Font size scale | `--rux-size-` | `--rux-size-4` |
| Font weight scale | `--rux-weight-` | `--rux-weight-medium` |
| Spacing scale | `--rux-space-` | `--rux-space-3` |
| Radius scale | `--rux-radius-` | `--rux-radius-2` |
| Motion (duration) | `--rux-duration-` | `--rux-duration-1` |
| Motion (easing) | `--rux-ease-` | `--rux-ease-1` |

**Rules:**
- Never use a Tier 1 token directly in component CSS. Always go through Tier 2.
- Use full color names: `blue`, `gray`, `red` — never `blu`, `gry`.
- `bg` is the one allowed abbreviation (universally understood).

---

## Tier 2 — Semantics

**Purpose:** Design-language roles. Maps Tier 1 values to intent.
Surfaces, text roles, borders, status colors, accent.

**Location:** `:root` in `variables.css`

**Naming:** `--rux-{category}-{role-or-number}`

| Category | Pattern | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| Surface elevations | `--rux-bg-{n}` | `--rux-bg-2` (higher = lighter in dark mode) |
| Text roles | `--rux-text-{n}` | `--rux-text-1` (primary), `--rux-text-2` (secondary) |
| Border roles | `--rux-border-{n}` | `--rux-border-2` (default) |
| Status colors | `--rux-status-{color}` | `--rux-status-red`, `--rux-status-green` |
| Accent | `--rux-color-accent` | — |

**Rules:**
- Component CSS references ONLY Tier 2 tokens (never Tier 1 directly).
- Tier 2 tokens have no component names in them — they describe roles, not elements.

---

## Tier 3 — Component

**Purpose:** Component-specific sizing, spacing, typography, and color. Defined once
at the top of a component file and consumed throughout that file.

**Location:** Top of the component's own CSS file — NOT in `variables.css`.

**Naming:** `--rux-{comp}-{property}` using the component's short prefix.

| Component | Prefix | File |
|-----------|--------|------|
| Button | `btn` | `button.css` |
| Form fields | `fld` | `form.css` |
| Trip bar | `trp` | `primitives.css` (or `tripbar.css`) |
| Panel / sidebar | `panel` | `layout.css` |
| Modal | `modal` | `modal.css` |
| Dropdown | `dd` | `dropdown.css` |

**Placement rule:**

```css
/* Single-selector component → scope to the class */
.btn {
  --rux-btn-height: 32px;
  height: var(--rux-btn-height);
}

/* Multi-selector component (e.g. input, select, textarea all share tokens)
   → :root block at the TOP of the component file */

/* form.css */
:root {
  --rux-fld-height:   28px;
  --rux-fld-radius:   var(--rux-radius-2);
  --rux-fld-bg:       var(--rux-bg-2);
  --rux-fld-shadow:   inset 0 2px 4px oklch(0% 0 0 / 35%);
}

input, select, textarea {
  height: var(--rux-fld-height);
  background: var(--rux-fld-bg);
}
```

**Rules:**
- Tier 3 tokens reference ONLY Tier 2 tokens or literal values.
- Never reference a Tier 1 token from a Tier 3 token.
- Never put a Tier 3 token in `variables.css`.

---

## The Anti-Pollution Rule

`variables.css` must contain zero component names.
Any token whose name includes `btn`, `fld`, `trp`, `panel`, `modal`, `tripbar`,
`card`, `bus`, `icon`, `header`, `badge`, `dropdown` — or any other UI element —
belongs in a component file, not in `variables.css`.

**When in doubt:** If you can draw the thing on screen, its tokens do not belong in
`variables.css`.

---

## What belongs in `variables.css`

```
✓  Color seeds            --rux-color-blue
✓  Font families          --rux-font-sans
✓  Size / weight scales   --rux-size-4, --rux-weight-medium
✓  Spacing / radius       --rux-space-3, --rux-radius-2
✓  Motion                 --rux-duration-1, --rux-ease-1
✓  Surface elevations     --rux-bg-1 … --rux-bg-5
✓  Text roles             --rux-text-1, --rux-text-2, --rux-text-3
✓  Border roles           --rux-border-1, --rux-border-2, --rux-border-3
✓  Status colors          --rux-status-red, --rux-status-green …
✓  Accent                 --rux-color-accent

✗  Button tokens          → button.css
✗  Field tokens           → form.css
✗  Trip bar tokens        → primitives.css
✗  Layout / panel tokens  → layout.css
✗  Z-index values         → layout.css
✗  Shadow recipes         → component file that uses them
✗  COMPAT / old aliases   → delete once callers are updated
```

---

## COMPAT Section (Temporary)

Migration aliases (old token names pointing to new ones) are allowed during
a transition, but must live at the bottom of `variables.css` under a clearly
marked `COMPAT` comment and must be deleted once the referencing files are
updated. A COMPAT section that has existed longer than one refactor cycle
should be treated as technical debt.

